data.title: Quaid-e-Azam Trophy 2023 squads: Full team lists, player news and injury replacement updates
data.text:
Eight teams will be participating in the 2023/24 Quaid-e-Azam Trophy, starting September 10. Here is all you need to know about the Quaid-e-Azam Trophy squads of each team, including full team lists, player news, and injury replacement updates.

Subscribe to the Wisden Cricket YouTube channel for post-match analysis, player interviews, and much more.

The 2023-24 Quaid-e-Azam Trophy, Pakistan’s premier first-class competition, will be hosted by Abbottabad, Lahore, and Rawalpindi. The season will mark the return of regional and departmental teams in accordance with the PCB 2014 Constitution.

Peshawar, Karachi Whites, Lahore Blues, Rawalpindi, FATA, Multan, Lahore Whites, and Faisalabad will play 29 matches.

The competition commences on September 10, and the top two sides will lock horns against each other in the final scheduled at the Gaddafi Stadium in Lahore from October 22 to 26.
